      "content": "You should absolutely increase your water intake to flush the lithium, but never increase the lithium dose on your own.\nLithium has a narrow therapeutic window, so taking extra without a blood test could lead to toxicity and permanent brain damage.\nStick to your prescribed schedule and drink more water, and if the mood swings persist, see your doctor for a blood level check rather than adjusting the dose yourself.",
